The Israeli Documentary Filmmakers Forum''' is an [[Israel]]i''' [[Nonprofit organization]] foster documentary films and series. The Israeli Documentary Filmmakers Forum include over 450 members.<ref name="fdoc">{{cite web|url=http://fdoc.org.il/English |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101128221735/http://www.fdoc.org.il/english |archive-date=2010-11-28 |dead-url=yes |title=פורום היוצרים הדוקומנטרים &#124; About The Israeli Documentary Filmmakers Forum |accessdate=2016-02-05 |df= }}</ref> In 2006 the forum initiated and organized an annual competition, called "The Israeli Documentary Film Competition".<ref> Carmel, Asaf (February 5, 2007). [http://www.haaretz.co.il/gallery/1.1383805 "Documentary films competition"] and Fisher, Shany (February 14, 2008). [http://e.walla.co.il/item/1234681 "Documentary films competition"]. [[Walla!]] </ref> The forum held a long-standing struggle to invest more money and get more broadcast time for original Israeli documentary projects in the Israeli television channels.<ref> Mena, Maya. Ben Nun, Sagi. Kayam, Tali (June 24, 2015). [http://b.walla.co.il/item/2866679 "The creators are going to war"]. [[Walla!]]. And Averbach, Li-Or (February 10, 2014). [http://www.globes.co.il/news/article.aspx?did=1000916012 "Baby boom is not documentary says the filmmakers forum"]. [[Globes]]. And [http://www.the7eye.org.il/verdicts/52978 " Israeli Documentary Filmmakers against President of Israel - bagaz verdict"]. [[HaAyin HaShevi'it]]. </ref>
The current forum's chairwoman is Osnat Trabelsi.<ref> Anderman, Nirit (August 5, 2015). [http://www.haaretz.com/life/movies-television/.premium-1.669562 "Now playing in Israel: film censorship"]. [[Haaretz]]. </ref> Her predecessors were [[Uri Rosenwaks]],<ref> Litman, Shany (February 17, 2014). [http://www.haaretz.co.il/gallery/cinema/.premium-1.2246419 "An Inreview with Uri Rosenwaks]. [[Haaretz]]. </ref> Avishai Kfir and Naftali Glicksberg.<ref> Kam, Anat (July 8, 2008). [http://b.walla.co.il/item/1310072 "Kfir instead of Glicksberg"]. [[Walla!]] </ref>
