{{refimprove|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox video game |title=SBK 08 Superbike World Championship |image=SBK-08 Superbike World Championship.jpg |caption= PC Boxart |developer=[[Black Bean Games]] |publisher=[[Milestone S.r.l.]] |designer= |engine= |released= {{vgrelease|EU|August 1, 2008|NA|November 8, 2008}}<ref>http://uk.gamespot.com/ps2/driving/sbk08superbikeworldchampionship/similar.html?mode=versions{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> |genre=[[Racing video game|Racing]] |modes=[[Single-player video game|Single-player]] & [[multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] |platforms= [[PlayStation 2]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation Portable]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Personal Computer|PC]] }}
'''''SBK-08: Superbike World Championship''''' (known as '''''SBK Superbike World Championship''''' in North America) is the official video game for the [[2008 Superbike World Championship season]]. It features 22 official riders and 12 official race tracks.
The game was going to be planned for the [[Nintendo DS]] and the [[Nintendo Wii]] but was cancelled.
The European version of [[PlayStation 3]] release lacked [[Playstation trophies]] support.
==Reception== SBK08 received mixed reviews, with an average of 65% on [[GameRankings]]. It's owest score was 55% from Play,<ref>Play magazine review, issue 172, [[Imagine Publishing]]</ref> and highest 7/10 from Total PC Gaming.
