'''Spellbound Pictures Ltd., USA LLC''' is a [[film]] and [[television]] [[Production company|production]] and [[Film distribution|distribution company]] founded by [[Mark McClafferty]] and [[Pamela Edwards McClafferty]] in 1996.
Spellbound Pictures completed a $60,000,000.00, 12 picture deal with Ellipse/Canal +, the French Entertainment giant in 1996 to supply the United Artist Theatre Circuit with a steady flow of family friendly films.<ref>Busch, Anita M. and Paul Smith: “UATC Gets Spellbound”, Page 5. ''Daily Variety'', Jan 18. 1996</ref> It was under this deal that Spellbound Pictures along with [[Mehra Entertainment]] completed ''[[The Climb (1999 film)|The Climb]]'', starring [[John Hurt]], [[Gregory Smith (actor)|Gregory Smith]], and [[David Strathairn]], which won eight international film festival awards and was released February 26, 1999.<ref name="IMDB">{{cite web | work=IMDB.com | title=The Climb | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0118865/ | accessdate=27 March 2009}}</ref>
