{{Infobox television | show_name = Tainted Dreams | image = Tainted Dreams title.png | caption = | creator = [[Sonia Blangiardo]] | writer = Lindsay Harrison | director = | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Alicia Minshew]] * [[Grant Aleksander]] * [[Kelley Menighan Hensley]] }} | country = United States | language = English | num_seasons = 1 | num_episodes = | list_episodes = | executive_producer = Sonia Blangiardo | producer = {{Plainlist| * Mark Costello (consulting) * Rob Santeramo (consulting) * Candy Straight (consulting) * Robert Levinstein (coordinating) * Teresa Cicala }} | cinematography = | runtime = | company = NYC Brand Productions | distributor = | network = [[YouTube]] | first_aired = {{start date|2013|12|30}} | last_aired = present | related = | website = http://tainteddreamstheseries.com }}
'''''Tainted Dreams''''' is a [[soap opera]] [[web series]] that premiered on [[YouTube]] on December 30, 2013. Created by [[Sonia Blangiardo]], it is a "soap-within-a-soap" which follows the backstage drama of the fictional soap opera ''Painted Dreams''.
''Tainted Dreams'' was nominated for a [[Daytime Emmy Award]] for [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding New Approaches Drama Series|Outstanding New Approaches Drama Series]] in 2014, and one for [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Digital Daytime Drama Series|Outstanding Digital Daytime Drama Series]] in 2017. [[Kelley Menighan Hensley]], Michael Lowry, [[Natalia Livingston]], and Anthony Wilkinson were also nominated for Daytime Emmys in 2017 for their performances.
==Cast== * [[Alicia Minshew]] as Angelica Caruso<ref name="Official characters">{{cite web |url=http://tainteddreamstheseries.com/about-tainted-dreams/characters/ |title=''Tainted Dreams'': Meet the Characters |publisher=TaintedDreamstheSeries.com |accessdate=November 12, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928134638/http://tainteddreamstheseries.com/about-tainted-dreams/characters/ |archivedate=September 28, 2015 |df= }}</ref> * Michael Lowry as Jordan Bradford<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Walt Willey]] as Gregory Ashford<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Kelley Menighan Hensley]] as Veronica Ashford<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Terri Ivens]] as Kassandra Bently<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Austin Peck]] as Max Hillstone<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Grant Aleksander]] as Adam Clark<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Natalia Livingston]] as Liza Park<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Ilene Kristen]] as Vivian Park<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Jessie Godderz]] as Dylan Buckwald<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Bobbie Eakes]] as Courtney Parish<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[James DePaiva]] as Eddy Parish<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Marnie Schulenburg]] as Peyton Adams<ref name="Official characters"/> * Anthony J. Wilkinson as Anthony DiGiacomo<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Dina Manzo]] as Alessandra DiGiacomo<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Colleen Zenk]] as Sofia DiGiacomo<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Nathan Purdee]] as Ethan Washington<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Larkin Malloy]] as Henry Steinman<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Tonja Walker]] as Tina Scott<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Lisa Marie Varon]] as Carla Santiago<ref name="Official characters"/> * [[Carolyn Hinsey]] as Herself<ref name="Official characters"/>
==Production and broadcast== Blangiardo created ''Tainted Dreams'' after the cancellation of the long running daytime soap opera ''[[One Life to Live]]'', where she was a producer.<ref name="Celebuzz Manzo">{{cite web |url=http://www.celebuzz.com/2013-01-30/dina-manzo-lands-acting-gig-on-soap-opera-inspired-series-exclusive/ |title=Dina Manzo Lands Acting Gig on Soap Opera-Inspired Series |date=January 30, 2013 |publisher=[[Celebuzz]] |first=Jethro |last=Nededog |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref><ref name="MF Manzo">{{cite web |url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/tainted-dreams-creator-sonia-blangiardo-i-was-struck-by-the-loss-of-this-unique-art-form-that-had-been-integral-to-nyc-casts-rhonj-dina-manzo-in-role/2013/01/30/ |title=''Tainted Dreams'' Creator Sonia Blangiardo: 'I Was Struck By The Loss Of This Unique Art Form That Had Been Integral To NYC!' |first=Michael |last=Fairman |work=[[On-Air On-Soaps]] |date=January 30, 2015 |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> She said in 2013, "I was struck by the loss of this unique art form that had been such an integral part of NYC for decades. I wanted to somehow capture my own two decades working behind the scenes of three different NYC-based soaps."<ref name="Celebuzz Manzo"/><ref name="MF Manzo"/>
First cast were Minshew, Lowry, Willey, Hensley and Schulenburg.<ref name="Celebuzz Manzo"/><ref name="MF Manzo"/> In January 2013, Manzo of [[Bravo (U.S. TV network)|Bravo]]'s ''[[The Real Housewives of New Jersey]]'' was cast as Alessandra DiGiacomo, a role written with her in mind.<ref name="Celebuzz Manzo"/><ref name="MF Manzo"/> Later cast additions in 2013 included Peck,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2013/03/11/austin-peck-joins-tainted-dreams |date=March 11, 2013 |work=[[Daytime Confidential]] |title=Austin Peck Joins ''Tainted Dreams'' |first=Luke |last=Kerr |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> Zenk,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/central-new-york/article/Colleen-Zenk-to-Lead-TAINTED-DREAMS-Dramedy-Hudson-Theatres-LOOPED-20130529# |title=Colleen Zenk to Lead ''Tainted Dreams'' Dramedy |publisher=BroadwayWorld.com |date=May 29, 2013 |accessdate=November 13, 2015}}</ref> Aleksander,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2013/06/13/guiding-lights-grant-aleksander-joins-tainted-dreams |date=June 13, 2013 |work=Daytime Confidential |title=''Guiding Light''{{'s}} Grant Aleksander Joins ''Tainted Dreams'' |first=Jillian |last=Bowe |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> Livingston,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2013/07/09/general-hospital-and-days-of-our-livexs-alum-natalia-livingston-joins-tainted-dreams |date=July 9, 2013 |work=Daytime Confidential |title=Natalia Livingston Joins ''Tainted Dreams'' |first=Jillian |last=Bowe |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> Malloy,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2013/07/16/former-all-my-childrens-larkin-malloy-joins-tainted-dreams |date=July 16, 2013 |work=Daytime Confidential |title=Former ''All My Children'' Star Larkin Malloy Joins ''Tainted Dreams'' |first=Jillian |last=Bowe |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> Eakes,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2013/07/30/soap-diva-bobbie-eakes-joins-tainted-dreams |date=July 30, 2013 |work=Daytime Confidential |title=Soap Diva Bobbie Eakes Joins ''Tainted Dreams''! |first=Jillian |last=Bowe |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> and DePaiva, Kristen and Walker.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2013/07/25/one-life-to-live-alums-join-tainted-dreams |date=July 25, 2013 |work=Daytime Confidential |title=''One Life to Live'' Alums Join ''Tainted Dreams'' |first=Jillian |last=Bowe |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref>
The first three episodes of ''Tainted Dreams'' were released on [[YouTube]] on December 30, 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/tainted-dreams-soap-1075062/? |date=December 30, 2013 |work=[[TV Guide]] |title=First Look: An All-Star Soap Cast Shines in ''Tainted Dreams'' |first=Michael |last=Logan |authorlink=Michael Logan (journalist) |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref>
''Tainted Dreams'' was licensed to [[Amazon.com]] for streaming through its [[Amazon Prime]] service starting December 26, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/New-Soap-Opera-Series-TAINTED-DREAMS-to-Premiere-on-Amazon-Prime-1226-20161220 |title=New Soap Opera Series TAINTED DREAMS to Premiere on Amazon Prime 12/26 |publisher=BroadwayWorld.com|date=December 20, 2016 |accessdate=December 20, 2016}}</ref>
